To draw a chessboard in LATEX, you can use the `chessboard` package. Here's an example of how to use it:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}

\begin{document}
\begin{chessboard}
\setboardsize{8cm}
\pieceset{white}{white}
\postion{start}
\end{chessboard}
\end{document}
```

This code will create a chessboard with a size of 8cm and white pieces. You can change the size and the color of the pieces by adjusting the corresponding options.

To add a FEN notation to the chessboard, you can use the `fen` package. Here's an example of how to use it:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard, fen}

\begin{document}
\begin{chessboard}
\setboardsize{8cm}
\pieceset{white}{white}
\postion{start}
\end{chessboard}

\fen{start}

\end{document}
```

This code will create a chessboard with a size of 8cm and white pieces, and then display the FEN notation `start` above the board. You can change the position of the FEN notation by adjusting the `above` option.

Note that the `chessboard` and `fen` packages are not compatible with each other, so you need to load them in this specific order. Also, the `chessboard` package requires the `graphicx` package to be loaded before it.

The final code would look like this:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{graphicx, chessboard, fen}

\begin{document}
\begin{chessboard}
\setboardsize{8cm}
\pieceset{white}{white}
\postion{start}
\end{chessboard}

\fen{start}

\end{document}
```

This code will create a chessboard with a size of 8cm and white pieces, and then display the FEN notation `start` above the board.
